e likes to be. She adopts her husband’s values. For a long time she is bribed and blinded by the sparkle of the diamonds. But possessions don’t fill the emptiness she feels. She knows she is going against her purpose, her destiny. She knows she is giving up something very precious, something no diamond can fill.  She  justifies this ,thinking that she is putting  the needs and comforts of the family ahead of her principles and the only way to go on in this charade is to convince herself that she wants the same things her husband wants. It takes a long time before she realizes that by giving up her dreams and values she is disappearing and is metamorphosed into a complete stranger. She realizes that   her children deserve to know her and be influenced by her views even if they are in conflict with her husband’s. Events in her life force her to make drastic changes and after loosing something very precious she finally embarks in a journey of the soul.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe book is about her journey to reclaim herself and to find the courage to shed any attachment she still has to the shines of the diamonds. She does this to give rebirth to her true self.','Book: Trapped in a Diamond','','inherit','open','open','','114-autosave-v1','','','2013-01-08 10:27:37','2013-01-08 15:27:37','',114,'http://fromnowon.ca/wp-draft1-s/114-autosave.html',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `bo1e_posts` VALUES (189,1,'2011-11-17 17:33:00','2011-11-17 22:33:00','<h5>Seven Signs You Are Losing Yourself In A Relationship\r\nby Vittoria Adhami</h5>\r\n<strong>Introduction</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-118\" title=\"book-cover\" src=\"http://fromnowon.ca/wp-draft1-s/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/book-cover.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"235\" height=\"340\" />First of all I want to tell you what is my philosophy of life. I believe that all experiences in life are GOOD. The ones we feel are negative should be used as learning lessons and the good experiences should be accepted as a blessings and a reminder that we are on the right path.\r\n\r\nThis book is for anyone that finds her or himself in a relationship where diversity in thoughts, culture or race, causes conflicts. It is a book for all the people that in order to be loved and accepted, choose to adapt the partner’s thoughts and values.\r\n\r\nThis book is dedicated to all the spouses that for whatever reason, for love or need, transform themselves into the person their partner wants rather than the person they can be. The loss of you, happens gradually without your awareness, the desire to be loved and accepted blinds you. It can be years and even decades before you realize that your true self is lost or that you were never allowed to discover it. I want this book to be an opportunity, for some of the readers who will identify themselves with all or some of my experiences, to find a point of inspiration and encouragement to take their lives into their own hands. I want you to find the courage to awake the true self who I assure you it will accompany you to the journey into the new life that YOU and only YOU will choose.\r\n\r\nThroughout my life I went through verbal, emotional and physical abuse. I have been very fortunate to also experience real love and most importantly I have been able to forgive.\r\n\r\nAfter the death of my first husband Aflatoun I discovered the secret life of my spouse and at the same time I realized that I had not only lost my husband, I had lost my past. The history I made with my spouse had to be rewritten. His death was a tragic event, but the loss of my identity while I was married to him was more tragic to me. I went through periods of hurt, doubts, discovery, forgiveness, and resignation and finally hope. Throughout this time I kept wearing a $40,000.0 diamond ring that my deceased husband had given me .I could not let go of it but the mysterious loss of it one day was incredibly revealing to me. It made me realize that I had being looking at life from the distorted internal perspective of the many facet of a diamond. The loss of the ring changed my perspective of life and I was inspired to write my first book <em>Trapped in a Diamond</em>.','Book: Trapped in a Diamond','','inherit','open','open','','114-revision-v1','','','2011-11-17 17:33:00','2011-11-17 22:33:00','',114,'http://fromnowon.ca/114-revision-5.html',0,'revision','',0);
